               <p>THOMAS PICKETT. I live in <placeName id="t18310630-164-crimeloc868">Anderson's-buildings, City-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-164-crimeloc868" type="placeName" value="Anderson's-buildings, City-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-164-crimeloc868" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-164-off866 t18310630-164-crimeloc868"></join> - I have a covered book-stall in front of my house. On the 26th of May I was sitting in my room: I saw the prisoner at my stall: before I got out he had gone off - I followed him, and he dropped a Bible, which I had missed; I saw it in his possession - I came up with him within twenty yards of my house: he had been carrying it wrapped in his apron - it has my mark in it; I had seen him before, and had missed books before.</p>
